ve-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran requested an emergency load of US$5&nbsp;billion from the [[International Monetary Fund]] for the first time since the 1960s to help combat the virus outbreak.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/12/iran-request-5-billion-emergency-loan-international-monetary/ |title=Iran requests $5&nbsp;billion emergency loan from International Monetary Fund to fight coronavirus pandemic |first=Roland |last=Oliphant |date=12 March 2020 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314013011/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/12/iran-request-5-billion-emergency-loan-international-monetary/ |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Khamenei said that the virus outbreak may be a \"biological attack\" on Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/iran-s-khamenei-says-virus-outbreak-may-be-biological-attack |title=Iran's Khamenei Says Virus Outbreak May Be 'Biological Attack' |first1=Yasna |last1=Haghdoost |first2=Golnar |last2=Motevalli |work=Bloomberg |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323123634/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/iran-s-khamenei-says-virus-outbreak-may-be-biological-attack |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*13 March: The Ministry of Health reported 1,289 more new confirmed cases and 85 new deaths. They also reported that 3,529 people had recovered so far. [[Nasser Shabani]], a senior commander of [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] (IRGC), has died from the virus.<ref name=\"shabani-dies\">{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Senior-Iranian-IRGC-commander-dies-of-coronavirus-.html |title=Senior Iranian IRGC commander dies of coronavirus |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=13 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314172342/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Senior-Iranian-IRGC-commander-dies-of-coronavirus-.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*14 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,365 more new confirmed cases and 97 new deaths. They also reported that 4,339 people had recovered so far. [[Minoo Mohraz]], a member of committee to combat Coronavirus, tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/14/Iran-Member-of-committee-to-combat-Coronavirus-tests-positive-for-the-virus.html |title=Iran: Member of committee to combat Coronavirus tests positive for the virus |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316012227/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/14/Iran-Member-of-committee-to-combat-Coronavirus-tests-positive-for-the-virus.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*15 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,209 more new confirmed cases and 113 new deaths. They also reported that 4,590 people had recovered so far. [[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]], a member of [[Assembly of Experts]], tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran Assembly of Experts member infected with coronavirus |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/15/Iran-Assembly-of-Experts-member-infected-with-coronavirus.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113238/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/15/Iran-Assembly-of-Experts-member-infected-with-coronavirus.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/718963|title=\u0641\u0631\u06cc\u0628\u0631\u0632 \u0631\u0626\u06cc\u0633 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u0627\u060c \u0627\u0642\u062a\u0635\u0627\u062f\u062f\u0627\u0646\u060c \u0628\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a|publisher=Asr Iran|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*16 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,053 more new confirmed cases and 129 new deaths. They also reported that 4,996 people had recovered so far. [[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]] and economist [[Fariborz Raisdana]] died from the virus.<ref name=\"golpayegani-dies\">{{cite news |title=Top Iranian cleric among those tasked with choosing supreme leader succumbs to coronavirus infection |url=https://www.rt.com/news/483203-iran-top-cleric-coronavirus/ |accessdate=16 March 2020 |agency=RT News |date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317040733/https://www.rt.com/news/483203-iran-top-cleric-coronavirus/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*17 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,178 more new confirmed cases and 135 new deaths. They also reported that 5,389 people had recovered so far. [[Sharif University]] published a study over number of possible casualties. Three scenarios were announced: If people cooperate now, Iran will see 120,000 infections and 12,000 deaths before the outbreak is over, if they offer medium cooperation, there will be 300,000 cases and 110,000 deaths. But if people fail to follow any guidance, it could collapse Iran's already strained medical system and there will be 4 million cases and 3.5 million deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|title=Iran warns virus could kill 'millions' in Islamic Republic|date=17 March 2020|website=AP NEWS|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318132446/https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Traditional Persian fire festival [[Chaharshanbe Suri]] were also banned by the government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/iran-bans-fire-festival-celebrations-over-virus/1769048|title=Iran bans fire festival celebrations over virus|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317180228/https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/iran-bans-fire-festival-celebrations-over-virus/1769048|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> About 85,000 prisoners were temporarily released due to the coronavirus, and two days later the government announced plans to pardon 11,000 prisoners, including those charged with political crimes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran frees 85,000 prisoners due to coronavirus, says judiciary spokesman |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/17/Iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-due-to-coronavirus-says-judiciary-spokesman.html |accessdate=18 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318141153/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/17/Iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-due-to-coronavirus-says-judiciary-spokesman.html |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/iran-to-pardon-10000-including-security-prisoners |title=Iran to pardon 10,000, including 'security' prisoners |first=Patrick |last=Wintour |date=19 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320191918/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/iran-to-pardon-10000-including-security-prisoners |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*18 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,192 more new confirmed cases and 147 new deaths. They also reported that 5,710 people had recovered so far. \n*19 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,046 more new confirmed cases and 149 new deaths. Former MP [[Hamid Kahram]] died from the coronavirus.<ref name=\"kahram-dies\">{{cite news |title=Former Iran MP Hamid Kahram dies from coronavirus |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/20/Former-Iran-MP-Hamid-Kahram-dies-from-coronavirus.html |accessdate=20 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320025009/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/20/Former-Iran-MP-Hamid-Kahram-dies-from-coronavirus.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*On 20 March, 1,237 new infections and 149 deaths were reported. Media reports suggested that heavy traffic continued for the Nowruz holiday. A government minister had warned that the crisis might continue for six months if the disease is not brought under control.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/20/iranian-new-year-self-isolate-covid-19 |title=Iranians ignore requests to stay home for new year celebrations |first=Patrick |last=Wintour |date= 20 March 2020 |work=The Guardian }}</ref>\n* On 24 March, a new peak of 1,762 new cases were announced with 122 deaths reported.  President Rouhani said that the number of patients admitted to hospitals in different provinces as well as deaths due to the virus had decreased, which he took to be promising.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/446297/Rouhani-claims-number-of-coronavirus-patients-deaths-decreasing |title=Rouhani claims number of coronavirus patients, deaths decreasing |date=24 March 2020 |work=Tehran Times }}</ref> Iran accused [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]] of being spies, and a team they had sent to Iran to help had been ordered to leave the country.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.msf.org/msf-surprised-iran-put-stop-our-covid-19-response |title=MSF 'deeply surprised' that Iranian authorities put a stop to our COVID-19 response |date=25 March 2020 |work=Medecins Sans Frontieres }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-rejects-foreign-virus-death-toll-nears-2000-200324202829056.html |title=Iran rejects 'foreign' help as virus death toll nears 2,000 |date=24 March 2020|publisher=Al Jazeera }}</ref>\n* On 25 March, with new cases surpassing 2,000 for the first time, the government warned of a \"second wave\" of infection.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-52039298 |title=Coronavirus: Iran bans internal travel to avert 'second wave'|date=25 March 2020 |work=BBC }}</ref>\n* On 26 March, Iranian Health Ministry announced that 2,389 more people had become infected, with 157 new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-toll/irans-death-toll-from-coronavirus-climbs-to-2234-ministry-idUSKBN21D18F |title=Iran's death toll from coronavirus climbs to 2,234: ministry |agency=Reuters |date= 26 March 2020 }}</ref>\n* On 27 March, daily new cases had increased to 2,926 with 144 deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/27reuters-health-coronavirus-iran.html |title=Iran's Death Toll From Coronavirus Rises to 2,378: Health Ministry|date=27 March 2020|agency=Reuters |work=The New York Times}}</ref> Iranian media reported that nearly 300 people had died and over a thousand became ill due to [[methanol poisoning]] in the belief that drinking the alcohol can kill the virus in the body. [[Associated Press]] gave figures of around 480 deaths and 2,850 others affected.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/ap-ml-virus-outbreak-iran-a-deadly-drink.html |title=In Iran, False Belief a Poison Fights Virus Kills Hundreds|agency=Associated Press |work=The New York Times|date=27 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020|archive-date=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://archive.is/f7RbN}}</ref> 70 inmates escaped Saqqez Prison in Kurdistan province.<ref name=riot_iran />\n* On 28 March, the number of new cases exceeded 3,000 for the first time (3,076), with 139 reported new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/iran-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-to-2-517/1783000 |title=Iran: Coronavirus death toll rises to 2,517first=Ahmet |last=Dursun |date=28 March 2020|publisher=Analou Agency }}</ref> Prisoners in the [[western Iran]]ian city of [[Hamadan]] rioted and escaped, using the coronavirus outbreak as a pretext according to Hamedan's prosecutor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irna.ir/news/83732426/\u062f\u0627\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646-\u0647\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0646-\u0644\u06cc\u062f\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u0646\u0627\u0622\u0631\u0627\u0645\u06cc-\u062f\u0631-\u0632\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0646-\u0627\u06cc\u0646-\u0634\u0647\u0631-\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc-\u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f|title=\u062f\u0627\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0647\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0646: \u0644\u06cc\u062f\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0646\u0627\u0622\u0631\u0627\u0645\u06cc \u062f\u0631 \u0632\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |work=IRNA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/coronavirus-iran-says-54-inmates-large-after-mass-jail-break |title=Coronavirus: Iran says 54 inmates at large after mass jail break |date=30 March 2020 |work=Middle East Eye }}</ref> Prisoners in the city of [[Mahabad]], in Iran's [[Kurds|Kurdish]] region, also attempted to escape.<ref>[https://www.avatoday.net/node/9307 More attempts of prison break reported from Iran]</ref>\n* On 29 March, 2,901 new cases and 123 new deaths were announced.<ref name=\"irna-29march\">{{cite news|url=https://en.irna.ir/news/83731895/Official-12-391-COVID19-infected-patients-recovered-in-Iran|title=Official: 12,391 COVID19-infected patients recovered in Iran|agency=Islamic Republic News Agency|date=29 March 2020|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref> President Rouhani defended his government's response to the crisis, and said that according to health experts and doctors in Iran, \"in some provinces, we have passed the peak [of the epidemic] and are on a downward trajectory\".<ref name=\"aljazeera29032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-coronavirus-deaths-rise-rouhani-hits-criticism-200329113250455.html |title=As Iran coronavirus deaths rise, Rouhani hits back at criticism |date=29 March 2020 |publisher=Al Jazeera }}</ref>\n*On 30 March, there was a [[Impact of the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic on prisons|prison riot]] in the south of the country. 100,000 prisoners have been released as a measure to contain the pandemic, but an estimated 50,000 people are still behind bars, including violent offenders and so called \"security cases\",dual nationals and others with Western ties.<ref name=riot_iran>[https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/jordan-releases-travelers-quarantined-dead-sea-hotels-69867295?cid=clicksource_76_null_headlines_hed Prisoners riot in Iran; Netanyahu goes into self-quarantine] By AMIR VAHDAT and ARON HELLER, Associated Press, 30 March 2020</ref>\n\n* Human rights activists have reported that during riots in different Iran's jails on 30 and 31 March, at least 20 prisoners were killed in two prisons in [[Ahwaz]], when the guards opened fire of the prisoners. Several other prisoners are reported killed in Shiban prison, also in Ahwaz.<ref>[https://en.radiofarda.com/a/activists-say-many-inmates-killed-in-iran-prison-disturbances/30523805.html Activists Say Many Inmates Killed In Iran Prison Disturbances]</ref>\n\n===April 2020===\n====1 to 15 April====\n2 April \u2013 President Rouhani warned that the country could fight the coronavirus pandemic for another year. 3,111 new infections raise Iran's total to 50,468. 124 new deaths bring the total to 3,160. 16,711 of those hospitalised have recovered.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/iran-warns-months-crisis-virus-deaths-reach-3-111855260.html Iran warns of months of crisis as virus deaths reach 3,160] AFP, 2 April 2020</ref>\n\n'''Death of a juvenile prisoner'''- On 3 April 2020, Rupert Colville, a spokesman for the [[United Nations Human Rights Commission]] expressed his worries about prison conditions in Iran. There has been riots in some of Iran's prisons, following the high spread of coronavirus in Iran including inside its prisons.  Colville's comment came after Daniel Zeinolabedini, an inmate in [[Mahabad]] prison, north east of Iran, died after he was beaten by prison guards.<ref>[https://en.radiofarda.com/a/un-high-commissioner-horrified-at-death-of-young-man-in-iran-prison/30529032.html UN High Commissioner 'Horrified' At Death Of Young Man In Iran Prison]</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|colors=#F46D43\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=19/2, 20/2, 21/2, 22/2, 23/2, 24/2, 25/2, 26/2, 27/2, 28/2, 29/2, 1/3, 2/3, 3/3, 4/3, 5/3, 6/3, 7/3, 8/3, 9/3, 10/3, 11/3, 12/3, 13/3, 14/3, 15/3, 16/3, 17/3, 18/3, 19/3, 20/3, 21/3, 22/3, 23/3, 24/3, 25/3, 26/3, 27/3, 28/3, 29/3, 30/3, 31/3, 1/4, 2/4, 3/4, 4/4, 4/5\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n|y1= , 2, 5, 18, 28, 43, 61, 95, 139, 245, 388, 593, 978, 1501, 2336, 2922, 3513, 4747, 5823, 6566, 7161, 8042, 9000, 10075, 11364, 12729, 13938, 14991, 16169, 17361, 18407, 19644, 20610, 21638, 23049, 24811, 27017, 29406, 32332, 35408, 38309, 41495, 44606, 47593, 50468, 53183, 55743, 58,226\n|y1Title=Total No. of cases\n|yGrid= |xGrid= \n}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|colors=#000000\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=19/2, 20/2, 21/2, 22/2, 23/2, 24/2, 25/2, 26/2, 27/2, 28/2, 29/2, 1/3, 2/3, 3/3, 4/3, 5/3, 6/3, 7/3, 8/3, 9/3, 10/3, 11/3, 12/3, 13/3, 14/3, 15/3, 16/3, 17/3, 18/3, 19/3, 20/3, 21/3, 22/3, 23/3, 24/3, 25/3, 26/3, 27/3, 28/3, 29/3, 30/3, 31/3, 1/4, 2/4, 3/4, 4/4, 4/5\n|yAxisTitle=No. of deaths\n|legend=Legend\n|y1= 2, 2, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16, 19, 26, 34, 43, 54, 66, 77, 92, 107, 124, 145, 194, 237, 291, 354, 429, 514, 611, 724, 853, 988,