], and will also stop issuing visas to Iranian citizens starting 28 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-russia-iran/russia-suspends-some-flights-between-russia-and-iran-over-coronavirus-idUSKCN20L2D3 |title=Russia suspends some flights between Russia and Iran over coronavirus |agency=Reuters |date=27 February 2020 |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303142334/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-russia-iran/russia-suspends-some-flights-between-russia-and-iran-over-coronavirus-idUSKCN20L2D3 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n \nOn 28 February, New Zealand and [[Belarus]] reported their first cases of COVID-19, both involving people who had traveled from Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/28/new-zealand-confirms-first-coronavirus-case |title=New Zealand confirms first coronavirus case |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=28 February 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229001239/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/28/new-zealand-confirms-first-coronavirus-case |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://eng.belta.by/society/view/belarus-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-128580-2020/ |title=Belarus confirms first case of coronavirus |date=28 February 202 |work=BelTa |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228223501/https://eng.belta.by/society/view/belarus-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-128580-2020/ |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> New Zealand announced temporary restrictions on people travelling from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/119899280/ministry-of-health-gives-latest-update-on-novel-coronavirus|title=Coronavirus: First case of virus in New Zealand|website=Stuff|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://we