a]]'' as \"Hollywood Godzilla\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xT-gs7bUlic|title=Godzilla The Game - PS4 Gameplay Trailer|last=|first=|work=Bandai Namco Entertainment America|date=|accessdate=May 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2015/07/13/godzilla-developer-was-so-passionate-about-their-favorite-monster-they-snuck-it-in-the-game/|title=Godzilla Developer Was So Passionate About Their Favorite Monster They Snuck It In The Game|last=Spencer|first=|work= Siliconera|date=July 13, 2015|accessdate=March 6, 2018}}</ref> In 2017, a short virtual reality experience titled ''Kong VR: Destination Skull Island'' was made available at 1500 Samsung retail demo locations, in 15 AMC theater locations, and Samsung VR stores.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/216300/experience-kong-vr-destination-skull-island/|title=Experience Kong VR: Destination Skull Island|first=Steve|last=Barton|work=Dread Central|date=February 28, 2019|accessdate=June 9, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=June 9, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609201616/https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/216300/experience-kong-vr-destination-skull-island/}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Title\n! Release date\n! Developer\n! Publisher\n! Note\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left\" | ''Godzilla: Crisis Defense''<ref>[http://www.godzilla-movies.com/news/godzilla-2014-crisis-defense-game-launched Godzilla (2014) 'Crisis Defense' Game Launched]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | May 7, 2014\n| Legendary\n| Legendary\n| Tie-in web game to ''Godzilla''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left\" | ''Godzilla: Strike Zone''<ref name=\"license\">{{cite web|url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2014/04/15/godzilla-2014-licensed-product-guide/|title=Godzilla (2014) Licensed Products Guide|work=SciFi Japan|date=|accessdate=August 3, 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | May 15, 2014\n| Warner Bros. Entertainment\n| Warner Bros. International Enterprises\n| Tie-in mobile game to ''Godzilla''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left\" | ''Godzilla: Smash 3''<ref name=\"license\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | May 16, 2014\n| Rogue Play\n| [[Pipeworks Software|Pipeworks]]\n| Tie-in mobile game to ''Godzilla''\n|}\n\n==Future==\n[[Steven S. DeKnight]] (director and co-writer of ''[[Pacific Rim: Uprising]]'') discussed about the possibility of a crossover between ''[[Pacific Rim (film)|Pacific Rim]]'' and the MonsterVerse, stating:\n\n{{quote|\"There's been a lot of discussion about that possibility [of crossing over]. And part of the big overall plan after the third movie we've talked about is that could happen, it's always a possibility. It's by far not a certainty; it's merely theoretical at this point.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://collider.com/pacific-rim-godzilla-king-kong-crossover-monsters-universe/#steven-s-deknight|title=Exclusive: \u2018Pacific Rim Uprising\u2019 Director Says Crossover with \u2018Godzilla\u2019 and \u2018King Kong\u2019 Is Possible|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|publisher=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex Media]]|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=October 20, 2017|accessdate=October 22, 2017}}</ref>}}\n\nIn March 2019, when asked about the future of the MonsterVerse, producer Alex Garcia stated:\n\n{{quote|\"It's one brick at a time, each piece has to be as good as it can be, so right now it's all focused on this [''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'' and ''Godzilla vs. Kong'']. But could there be? Yeah, that's the hope if the movies turn out really well.\"{{sfn|Mirjahangir|2019|loc=21:30}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.godzilla-movies.com/news/legendary-wants-monsterverse-continue-after-godzilla-vs-kong-2020|title=Legendary wants the MonsterVerse to Continue after Godzilla vs. Kong in 2020|work=Scified|accessdate=March 25, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=March 25, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326044423/http://www.godzilla-movies.com/news/legendary-wants-monsterverse-continue-after-godzilla-vs-kong-2020}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Pacific Rim (film)|''Pacific Rim'']]\n* [[Kaiju]]\n\n==References==\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|refs=\n}}\n\n===Sources===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Bernstein|first=Abbie|year=2019|title=The Art of Godzilla: King of the Monsters|publisher=Titan Books|isbn=1789090687|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite AV media|first=Chris|last=Mirjahangir|title=Interview with Alex Garcia and Zach Shield|type=Audio|publisher=Toho Kingdom|year=2019|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{MonsterVerse}}\n{{Godzilla}}\n{{KingKong}}\n\n[[Category:Kaiju films]]\n[[Category:Godzilla films]]\n[[Category:King Kong films]]\n[[Category:Monster movies]]\n[[Category:Films about nuclear war and weapons]]\n[[Category:Media franchises introduced in 2014]]\n[[Category:Apocalyptic films]]\n[[Category:American disaster films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Fictional universes]]\n[[Category:Horror film franchises]]\n[[Category:Action film franchises]]\n[[Category:Godzilla|*]]\n[[Category:Kaiju]]\n[[Category:Giant monster films]]\n[[Category:King Kong|*]]\n[[Category:MonsterVerse| ]]\n", "name_user": "Brojam", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MonsterVerse"}
{"title_page": "List of firefighting films", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe following criteria qualify a film for inclusion on this list:\n\n* Primary plot of film regards firefighting or related fire/rescue service work in general.\n* Primary plot of the film involves firefighters or their personal lives as affected by their firefighting.\n* Noteworthy attention is given to firefighting activities.\n\nThis list includes documentaries and TV series.\n\n== Fiction ==\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* ''[[15 Minutes]]'' (2001)\n* ''911'' (TV 2018)\n* ''The 119'' (TV 1987) (unaired)\n* ''[[A Dangerous Summer]]'' (A.K.A. ''Flash Fire''; 1981)\n* ''Ablaze'' (2000)\n* [[Ablaze (film)|''Ablaze'']] (2001)\n* ''[[The Accidental Husband]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Always (1989 film)|Always]]'' (1989)\n* ''[[As the Light Goes Out]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Backdraft (film)|Backdraft]]'' (1991)\n* ''[[Bad Day on the Block]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[The Bells Go Down]]'' (1943)\n* ''[[Blue Smoke]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Burning Flame]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[Chicago Fire (TV series)|Chicago Fire]]'' (TV 2012)\n* ''[[City on Fire (1979 film)|City on Fire]]'' (1979)\n* ''[[Code Red (U.S. TV series)|Code Red]]'' (TV 1981)\n* ''[[Collateral Damage (film)|Collateral Damage]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Emergency!]]'' (TV 1972)\n* ''[[Emergency!|Emergency: The Convention]]'' (TV 1979)\n* ''[[Emergency!|Emergency: Greatest Rescues of Emergency!]]'' (TV 1979)\n* ''[[Emergency!|Emergency: Most Deadly Passage]]'' (TV 1978)\n* ''[[Emergency!|Emergency: The Steel Inferno]]'' (TV 1978)\n* ''[[Emergency!|Emergency: Survival on Charter #220]]'' (TV 1978)\n* ''[[Emergency!|Emergency: What's a Nice Girl Like You Doing...]]'' (TV 1979)\n* ''The Fallen'' (2009)\n* ''[[False Alarms (film)|False Alarms]]'' (1936)\n* ''[[Fire! (1901 film)|Fire!]]'' (1901)\n* ''[[Fire! (1977 film)|Fire!]]'' (TV 1977)\n* ''The Fire Alarm'' (1935)\n* ''The Fire Brigade'' (1926)\n* ''Fire Cheese'' (1941)\n* ''Fire on Kelly Mountain'' (TV 1973)\n*